1. Chosen Development Model
Model: Agile
Justification: We chose the agile model because it is flexible and easy to adapt. Since the project requirements can change during development, Agile allows us to make updates without affecting the whole system.

2. User Requirements
a. Stakeholders (WHO is involved)
• Teachers
Use the system to record attendance, enter grades, and communicate with students. They want to reduce paperwork and save time.
• Students
Access their grades, schedules, and announcements. They want quick and easy access to their school information.
b. User Stories (WHAT they need and WHY)
As a teacher, I want to mark attendance online so that I don’t need to use paper registers.
As a teacher, I want to enter student grades so that students can see their results easily.
As a student, I want to check my grades online so that I can track my performance.
As a student, I want to see my class schedule so that I know when my lessons are.

