e. Security Measures
Authentication:
Users (students and teachers) must log in with a valid username/email and password.
Role-based access control ensures that students and teachers can only access features allowed for their role.
Password Protection
Passwords are encrypted (hashed) before being stored in the database.
This prevents unauthorized access even if the database is compromised.
Data Protection
Sensitive information such as grades, attendance, and document requests is protected in the database.
Students cannot see other students’ personal information.
Secure Communication
Data transmitted between the frontend and backend is encrypted using HTTPS to prevent interception.
Access Control
Only teachers can mark attendance, enter grades, and approve/reject document requests.
Students can only view their own information and submit requests.
Error Handling
Unauthorized access attempts trigger error messages without revealing system details.
Audit Logging
Important actions such as attendance updates, grade entries, and document approvals are logged for accountability.

Summary:
These measures ensure that the system is secure, reliable, and protects the privacy of students and teachers while preventing unauthorized access.
